title: With a couple tweaks easily the best game on the App Store
author: Jojomoz
review:
The great thing about this game is that it's more fast paced than flappy bird and you can unlock items which the skater wears. The only problem so far is that the advertisements are in the way of where you tap so you end up tapping the advertisement mid game and get redirected or the skater doesn't jump. Please add an option to remove in game advertisement by purchasing or at least a way to move the advertisement in a different place. When this is done the game will truly be worthy of 5 stars. Also more boards to unlock would be cool and a setting to select what accessories you want to equip your skater with 

- thanks for taking my points into consideration 
- joe

title: Checking myself into rehab

title: Stuck.
author: kcraven01
review: I have to admit, this game is very entertaining. But, I had an issue with it. I was playing it and I decided to get out of it. So I pressed the home button, didn't work. I tried the power button, didn't work. I tried to do a hard restart but even that didn't work at first. After a few more tries I finally got my phone to restart. This might not happen to everyone, this is just a warning

title: Not Working
author: Random iPhone User123
review:
I recently downloaded the app, and then opened it. When I did, I went to the start screen. I attempted to hold my finger down on my iPhone, like the app suggested, but it didn't work and the app closed. I tried this a few times, and nothing worked, I then deleted the app.
I would assume that this is a rare issue, and mostly likely a bug. I personally feel that I cannot unfairly rate an app due to it not working correctly, because then I do not get to experience what the creator of this game originally intended,
And it would be unfair to give a 1 star rating to an app that I never got to use.
I rated this app 5 stars because I feel that I would have enjoyed this app, if I would have been able to use it.
- Random iPhone User123
